(192, 'References: - Andy and Sandeep’s investment viewed as positive signal - Mentioned comparable models: - VRBO (US) - Stanza - Quintu - FastFox - [Housing.com/CommonFloor](http://housing.com/CommonFloor) **CV:** WM – non incremental points below. ?? Not compounding – feels very inside out. ?? Cannot sell – and this needs a ton of capital ?? All over the place in a prop that he has designed ?? unsure he will get hands dirty and build it out **TD:** **KK:** **NS:** **Spiky: **0 **EF/FF: **EO (insights of an FF) **Founder Archetype: **6 **FMF: **7 **Thesis: **6 ? No spike, inside out thinking. ? No baseline research from supply or demand side. ? Inarticulate, overcomplicated explanation of a straightforward business model. ? No unique insights being a potential EO. <u>**Meeting Notes**</u> **Team** - [Sahil](https://www.linkedin.com/in/sahilludhani/) (Co-founder) - SRCC grad (2009) - Ex-Zomato: International expansion (launched NZ, Malaysia, Indonesia, Philippines) - Led CloudKitchens & Zomato Gold verticals - Ex-Stanza: Led operations, sales strategy, and supply - [Ashutosh](https://www.linkedin.com/in/ashutosh-tandon/) (Co-founder) - SRCC grad (2012) - Ex-Zomato: Sales & global growth team - Ex-CRED: Built CRED Store - Scaled to 1.5M orders/month - 5-6M monthly users (50% of CRED users) **Problem** - Real estate rental market stuck in “classifieds 1.0” - High friction rental process for both owners & tenants - Large security deposits (4-6 months) blocking access - No standardized...'),
(193, 'Final view 2026-01-09T10:28:00.000+05:30: 1. Trupti is the OG at CRED 1. TD had also emailed about this investment but we are late to it 1. Also, late in DeVC Fund I cycle to consider 1. They are selling to USA and neither is moving to USA 1. Next will be Z47 company 1. From @Aakash 1. Didn''t get over the line given past context of them meandering through multiple thesis areas and co-founder mix. 1. Didnt meet the current (near end of fund cycle) bar on AI bets. 1. Trupthi is a great cred OG crew person, but both seemed non-committal to a full US shift and double down. 1. We should be tracking from Z for sure.'),
(194, 'Current Product: AI Agent for ML Development: - Building “Emily” (MLE) - AI agent that replaces ML developers - Core value prop: One good ML developer + agent = work of 5 developers - Target market: Companies spending $2.5M+ on ML talent (5 developers) - Key differentiator vs AutoML: Can reason through ML problems and generate new strategies, not just hyperparameter search
heads up note 2025-08-29T12:43:00.000+05:30 by @Rahul Mathur: Hi team, Sharing the heads-up note for our investment in [Hexo AI](https://hexo.ai/). This is an AI agent which builds ML pipelines & workflows; it is similar to the coding Devin agent - acts like a member of your ML team DeVC is investing $50K as part of a $3M SAFE round @ $15M post money valuation (standard YC SAFE terms) Note: This is a toe-hold into the company; Cash & I are doing more work (e.g. BRCs, expert chats, network introductions & co-investor connects) & seek to form this round after meeting the founder in SF; we have got positive signal from Soumyadeep (DashReels, Z47 portfolio) and Sudarshan (Smallest AI, DeVC portfolio) **Founders** 1. [Kunal Bhatia](https://www.linkedin.com/in/kunalbhatia91/) - CEO 1. BITS ‘12 - MSc Economics graduate 1. 1.5 YOE as CoFo @ SuperLearn 1. Netflix-like learning platform, 100K users, shut down post-COVID when demand evaporated 1. 4.5 YOE as independent consultant on GovTech projects 1. Built grievance system processing 60M complaints for UP Chief Minister 1. [Vignesh Baskaran](https://www.linkedin.com...'),
(195, 'Dhairen - First Meeting - 2026-02-25: Source: DT via SPC India. Founder is SPC fellow. DT Views: ++ Past track record - 2x founder, Bugle acquired by Acceldata ++ GTM wedge identified through company research platform (Empor) +? Acceldata refs needed to calibrate ?? Urgency and courage of conviction - why not put in own money and hire? ?? Real differentiation ?? Why isn''t SPC leaning in here already --- SHAN''S BACKGROUND - 2x founder with strong technical background - 8 years at Google (Maps search, launched "One Today" product) - Built AI company Bugle (acquired by Acceldata during COVID) - Head of AI/ML at Acceldata for 1+ year post-acquisition PRODUCT EVOLUTION: EMPOR TO HEYFINN Started with Empor (company research website): - Built for personal investing research - 40k organic users, $0 marketing spend - Viral among portfolio managers globally - Compresses initial research time from half-day to 1 hour Discovered real pain point through customer conversations: - Portfolio managers need junior analyst capabilities - Typical junior analyst costs $150k-300k annually - Universe limitation: ~200 stocks vs 10k+ investable globally HEYFINN PRODUCT DETAILS Positioning: AI junior research analyst - 45 days old, 6 professional portfolio managers using it - 5 users outside India, including JP Morgan London manager - $10k annual pricing (customer wants $20k) Core capabilities: - Autonomous monitoring (earnings, management changes, analyst reports) - Adjacent stock investigation based ...'),
(198, 'Ref from [Gaurav Shahlot](https://www.linkedin.com/in/gauravshahlot/) (CPO at Khatabook): <u>Context</u>: Gaurav hired Varun into Khatabook 1. he''s got super strong product chops 1. really good at identifying and breaking down problem statements 1. Was good at talking to users & finding opportunities to move the needle on core metrics. 1. Extremely good at working with engineers and people in general. 1. I would totally trust him to build top notch products. 1. Was one of the stronger PMs in my team. 1. **The only callout from my side would be he gets excited by something new & interesting but could lose interest over time.** ---
Notes:: 1. Journey since last conversation 1. Decided to NOT pursue the BFSI x Indian market 1. Came to SFO 1. Worked on some Enterprise ideas - realized that there is no RTW 1. Now focusing on Consumer AI 1. What in Consumer AI? 1. Companion space 1. Approaching it from a proactive AI lens 1. Context & memory across apps (? how is unclear?) 1. Thinking about the accountability space e.g. go to the gym or do some work 1. Very early thoughts 1. Why come to SF? 1. Felt learnings were saturated 1. All VCs suggested that they move to SFO for learning 1. Fundraise situation 1. Raised ~$10K as an Angel round 1. Would spend ~80% of it over next 2 months 1. Looking to do a small $500K Pre-Seed 1. Action items 1. Get introduced to his father who is GCC head for Exxon Mobil in India 1. Introduce him to Riverline AI to beat some sense into the kids ---')
