(200, 'Meeting Notes (17 Feb - Gurgaon Office) - 2026-02-26: TARUN''S BACKGROUND & POLICY BAZAAR JOURNEY: - 13 years in ecosystem, started with comparison websites and SEO/SEM - Built revenue models through Google AdSense, then booking engines - Set up Affle''s partnership platform in India - worked with 500+ brands creating performance marketing and partnership models POLICY BAZAAR ACHIEVEMENTS: - Term insurance: Increased commissions from Rs 700 to Rs 3,400 per transaction in 1.5 years - Investment products: Built high-IRR products (15-18%) competing with mutual funds - Motor insurance: Created CURE model, became contribution positive - Health insurance: Developed "one crore health person" product with 15% additional premium - Key insight: One RM per customer dramatically improves NPS/CSAT and purchase control - Health persistency increased from 70-72% to current levels through dedicated RM - Cross-sell ratios improved from 1.4-1.5x to 2.6x transactions, 4x revenue HULP''S CORE CONCEPT & TARGET MARKET: - Personal assistance for modern families - "Can we take away all the pain in your life?" - Target: Parents with two kids not living with their own parents (dual-income households with Rs 70L+ income) - Subscription model at Rs 3,000-5,000/month - One PA managing 12 families initially, scaling to 25-27 families by year three - Architecture: PA as front-end with specialized desks (travel, maid coordination, government forms) in backend THREE CORE PRODUCT PILLARS FOR DAILY USAGE: 1. Meal...'),
(201, 'Notes:: Dr Marcus Setup clinic and the firm about 5 years ago. Focus is health span and not life span: life span is for only the top echelon and low accessible to all. Health span is the focus where you create widespread impact/effects - Supplements have low barrier to entry and low regulation - Devices increasingly exploding in terms of market size; but increasingly commoditized - Diagnostics is high capex and continuous iteration - Clinics is also high capex - so didn''t think about opening chain of clinics - Saw opportunity in data - wearables driving + diagnostic/blood based testing on the rise People are creating data but don''t know what to do with it. Device agnostic centralized intelligence is a value prop. Building a purely digital first experience + partnered with 1mg thyrocare etc have integrated all devices: whoop, garmin etc etc Collect data into central system - scrub and process it - then build a clinical dashboard for end user "Man in the middle approach" - doc/expert validates the output of rule engine (intellectually notes "it''s not ML yet broadly a rule engine") Positive surprise on hypothesis: willingness of people to try Sick care network fragility during pandemic has pushed people to try lifestyle first Increased willingness combined with social media has also created confusion Science and authenticity is the key invite driver: people see the difference between nutritionist vs a clinical practice "we are the only company in India (comparable in US peter in...'),
