(207, 'AI Notes:: This meeting was an investment evaluation call with Nirav, founder of Ignosis, an Account Aggregator (AA) orchestration and analytics platform in India''s fintech sector. Company Background: - Nirav founded Ignosis in January 2022 after running Pyramid FinTech (IT services company) - He''s selling Pyramid (~50 Cr valuation) to focus on Ignosis - Previously spent 12 years in New York working in fintech - Based in Ahmedabad with 30-person team (24 tech, 6 non-tech) - Co-founder Chintan handles tech while Nirav handles business - Hiring strategy: Recruit locally from colleges and groom young talent Product & Technology: - Provides AA orchestration across multiple Account Aggregators - Creates 20% improvement in AA conversion rates through intelligent routing - Core analytics layer categorizes transactions, identifies income, spending patterns - Offers white-labeled Personal Finance Management (PFM) solutions - Integrates deeply with clients'' loan origination systems - Competitive advantage: Real-time categorization engine with continuous improvement Business Model & Traction: - 50+ clients with only one churn - ~15-16 crore annual revenue - Two main revenue streams: - Lending analytics (60% of revenue): ₹4-7 per fetch - PFM solutions (40% of revenue): ~₹1-1.5 per active user monthly - MobiKwik is largest customer (40L active users, ~₹40L monthly revenue) - Transaction-level margins around 70% - Profitable, but raising capital for potential AA license acquisition Competi...'),
